sections.text:
The basis for excluding studies from the scoping review will be if any of the following criteria are met:
1. only informal diagnosis of ADHD (e.g. from a parent’s or teacher’s report or any ADHD
rating scale other than the DSM or ICD criteria);
2. only participants under 10 or over 19 years old, or no possibility for extracting data for the
age group of interest;
3. no possibility to extract data only for the ADHD subgroup (in studies with comorbid
ADHD);
4. no use of any of the following terms for the variables of interest: psychosocial functioning,
social functioning, family functioning, school functioning, academic functioning, peer functioning, peer group functioning, or adequate grammatical forms;
5. paper in a language other than English (see the Search strategy section for details);
6. non-peer reviewed journal;
7. research published before 1987 (see the Search strategy section for details);
8. no possibility to access the full version of the text or the data being searched.
